A man's body was on Saturday morning found floating in Teregana river in Kuresoi south, Nakuru county.The deceased is said to have been too drunk to cross the river after going on a drinking spree on Friday.Keringet chief Nicholas Kering said the man was a father of three.By the time of going to press the deceased's body was yet to be removed. But a senior police officer at Keringet station said they were sending officers to the scene.The officer said they will also investigate the incident.The area is known for illicit brews despite several raids to eradicate the vice.